category=Getting Started
description=<p>This example shows you how to check the current screen resolution.  For example, your application may require a certain minimum screen size, e.g. 1024x768 to work. If the application is started up on a system with a too-small screen, it should display an error message, then quit.</p>
discussion=<p>This custom command is used with the following statement:</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>  <font face="Courier" size="11">checkForScreenSize</font></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>You might call it in a stack's startup or <font face="Courier" size="11">preOpenStack</font> handler.:</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><font face="Courier" size="11">  </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#980517">on</font><font face="Courier" size="11"> openStack</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier" size="11">    checkForScreenSize</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier" size="11">  </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#980517">end</font><font face="Courier" size="11"> openStack</font></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>This handler is simple, taking no parameters. It checks the last two items of <font face="Courier" size="11">the </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#F88017">screenRect</font> function--the width and height of the main screen. If the main screen is smaller than 1024x768 pixels, in either dimension, it quits the application after displaying a dialog box with an explanation.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>This example quits the application if the specified condition isn't met. Of course, you should use such a handler only if your application actually requires a screen of this size. If the application does not actually require this screen size, but does work better with a large screen, it's better to display a dialog box but not quit the program, in case the user prefers to continue with the lower resolution (or has a screen that can't be used at high resolution).</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>You can write a similar handler to check for any condition that your application requires. For example, here is a variation to use if your application requires QuickTime 3.0 to be installed:</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><font face="Courier" size="11">  </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#980517">on</font><font face="Courier" size="11"> checkForQuickTime</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier" size="11">    </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#980517">if</font><font face="Courier" size="11"> the </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#F88017">QTVersion</font><font face="Courier" size="11"> &lt; 3.0 </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#980517">then</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier" size="11">      </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#0000FF">answer</font><font face="Courier" size="11"> &quot;SuperApp requires QuickTime 3.0.&quot; </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#980517">with</font><font face="Courier" size="11"> &quot;Sorry&quot;</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier" size="11">      </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#0000FF">quit</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier" size="11">    </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#980517">end</font><font face="Courier" size="11"> </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#980517">if</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier" size="11">  </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#980517">end</font><font face="Courier" size="11"> checkForQuickTime</font></p>
level=2
licensed=false
name=Check whether the screen resolution is high enough
solution=<p><font color="#980517">on</font> checkForScreenSize</p>\n<p>  <font color="#980517">if</font> item 3 of the <font color="#F88017">screenRect</font> &lt; 1024 \\</p>\n<p>     or item 4 of the <font color="#F88017">screenRect</font> &lt; 768 <font color="#980517">then</font></p>\n<p>    <font color="#0000FF">answer</font> error &quot;MyApp requires a 1024x768 or larger screen.&quot; \\</p>\n<p>       <font color="#980517">with</font> &quot;Sorry&quot;</p>\n<p>    <font color="#0000FF">quit</font></p>\n<p>  <font color="#980517">end</font> <font color="#980517">if</font></p>\n<p><font color="#980517">end</font> checkForScreenSize</p>
title=Check whether the screen resolution is high enough